First read in the MAJIQ results file and reformat it for easier parsing

How many NETs have differential splicing between the 12 tissues tested?

# Read in the NET lists
all_nets <-fread("../../stuff_fromeric/netlist_nets.bed",header=TRUE, sep="\t")
nemm_nets <- fread("../../stuff_fromeric/NEMMnetlist_nets.bed", header=TRUE,sep="\t")
predtm_nets <- fread("../../stuff_fromeric/PREDnetlist_nets.bed",header=TRUE,sep="\t")
rafals_nets <- fread("../../Rafel_coord",header=FALSE,sep="\t")
  
all_nets_list <- unique(all_nets$mouse)
nemm_nets_list <- unique(nemm_nets$mouse)
predtm_nets_list <- unique(predtm_nets$mouse)
rafals_nets_list <- rafals_nets$V5
# Pull out the NETs from the MAJIQ paper results
all_nets_results <- results[which(results[[1]] %in% all_nets_list),]

predtm_nets_results <- results[which(results[[1]] %in% predtm_nets_list),]
rafals_nets_results <- results[which(results[[1]] %in% rafals_nets_list),]

Are NETs enriched for alternative splicing compared to other genes?

# Number of protein-coding genes in MM10 = 22,597 (from ENSEMBL website)
annot_genes = 22597
# Take away the number of potential NETs
annot_genes = annot_genes-total_net
# Number of genes that display alternative splicing between at least 2/12 mouse tissues
alt_splice = length(unique(results$temp...1.))
alt_splice = alt_splice-spliced_net
genes_notsplice = annot_genes-alt_splice
# Fraction
all_gene = alt_splice/annot_genes
# Total NET genes
total_net = length(unique(all_nets_list))
spliced_net = length(unique(all_nets_results$temp...1.))
# Fraction
all_net = spliced_net/total_net
# NE > MM net list
total_nemm = length(unique(nemm_nets_list))
spliced_nemm = length(unique(nemm_nets_results$temp...1.))
# Fraction
all_nemm = spliced_nemm/total_nemm
# Total NET genes
total_predtm = length(unique(predtm_nets_list))
spliced_predtm = length(unique(predtm_nets_results$temp...1.))
all_predtm = spliced_predtm/total_predtm
labels <- c("All coding genes \n(minus potential NETs)","All coding genes \n(minus potential NETs)","All potential NETs","All potential NETs","NE > MM NETs", "NE > MM NETs","Pred TM NETs","Pred TM NETs")
values <- c(alt_splice,genes_notsplice,spliced_net,(total_net-spliced_net),spliced_nemm,(total_nemm-spliced_nemm),spliced_predtm,(total_predtm-spliced_predtm))
splice <- c("Spliced","Not spliced","Spliced", "Not spliced", "Spliced","Not spliced","Spliced", "Not spliced")
enrichment <- data.frame(labels,values,splice)
enrichment
ggplot(enrichment,aes(x = enrichment$labels, y = enrichment$value,fill = splice)) + 
    geom_bar(position = "fill",stat = "identity") +
    # or:
    # geom_bar(position = position_fill(), stat = "identity") 
    scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format()) +
    ylab("Proportion of genes alternatively spliced") +
    xlab(NULL) +
    ggtitle("NETs are enriched for tissue-specific alternative splicing \ncompared to other protein-coding genes")

How many LSVs occur in NETs between all the tissues tested?

netheatmap <- data.frame(sapply(nemm_nets_results[,16:81], function(x)(length(na.omit(x)))))
tissuenet <- t(data.frame(stri_split_fixed(str=rownames(netheatmap),pattern="_",n=3)))
heatmap_net <- data.frame(netheatmap,tissuenet[,1],tissuenet[,2])
#heatmap2$tissue1...2. <- factor(heatmap2$tissue1...2., levels=c("mus","hrt","lun","wfat","adr","aor","bfat","liv","kid","bstm","hyp","cer"))
#heatmap2$tissue1...1. <- factor(heatmap2$tissue1...1., levels=c("mus","hrt","lun","wfat","adr","aor","bfat","liv","kid","bstm","hyp","cer"))
# Using code from http://pseudofish.com/triangle-heatmaps-in-r-using-ggplot.html
net_heatmap <- ggplot(heatmap_net, aes(heatmap_net$tissuenet...2., heatmap_net$tissuenet...1.)) +
    ggtitle('Number of changing LSVs in NET genes between mouse tissues') +
    theme_bw() +
    xlab(NULL) +
    ylab(NULL) +
    geom_tile(aes(fill = heatmap_net$sapply.nemm_nets_results...16.81...function.x...length.na.omit.x....), color='white') +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = 'lightyellow', high = 'red', space = 'Lab') +
    geom_text(aes(label = heatmap_net$sapply.nemm_nets_results...16.81...function.x...length.na.omit.x....)) +
    theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
    theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) +
    theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90),
          axis.ticks=element_blank(),
          axis.line=element_blank(),
          panel.border=element_blank())

minusnetheatmap <- data.frame(sapply(minus_nets_results[,16:81], function(x)(length(na.omit(x)))))
minustissuenet <- t(data.frame(stri_split_fixed(str=rownames(minusnetheatmap),pattern="_",n=3)))
heatmap_netminus <- data.frame(minusnetheatmap,minustissuenet[,1],minustissuenet[,2])
#heatmap2$tissue1...2. <- factor(heatmap2$tissue1...2., levels=c("mus","hrt","lun","wfat","adr","aor","bfat","liv","kid","bstm","hyp","cer"))
#heatmap2$tissue1...1. <- factor(heatmap2$tissue1...1., levels=c("mus","hrt","lun","wfat","adr","aor","bfat","liv","kid","bstm","hyp","cer"))
